Temporary infrastructure works have started in Newcastle East to prepare for the Supercars Thrifty Newcastle 500 event.

Road and park users should prepare for changes to traffic conditions over a nine-week period. Regular updates will be provided in further weekly build notices. 


• Wharf Road from Watt Street to Horseshoe Beach Road will be closed from 7am Wednesday 1 February until 5pm Friday 31st March, 2023

• Horseshoe Beach Road – Temporary closures or lane restrictions. Nobbys Beach (West) carparks will be closed

• Temporary closures or lane restrictions will be in place on Scott Street, Parnell Place and Nobbys Road.


Special event clearway parking restrictions

The below special event clearway parking restrictions are in place from 6am to 6pm Monday 20 to Saturday 25 March;

  • Nobbys Road between Fort Drive south and Fort Drive
  • Parnell Place between Scott Street and Fort Drive south

A clearway map is attached.


What are special event clearways?

Clearways are strict no-parking zones and apply to all vehicles, including residents with local parking permits and Mobility Scheme Permit holders. They are put in place to provide extra road space for the event and to remove vehicles from the precinct for public safety.

Temporary traffic changes around the University of Wollongong and TAFE NSW will be in place from Monday 27 February 2023 for approximately six weeks, to minimise congestion for the start of the university year. 


The temporary traffic changes are as follows:

  • M1 southbound traffic exiting at University Avenue will be diverted left, to make a U-turn at the eastern roundabout, between 7.45am and 9.15am on weekdays. 
  • Traffic at Irvine Street will be diverted to the University Western Access route via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road during peak periods.  
  • Motorists accessing the M1 northbound ramp (towards Sydney) at Northfields Avenue during peak periods will be diverted via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road.  

Bus access from University Avenue into Irvine Street will not be affected during diversions and outside peak periods traffic will continue to access the University via Irvine Street and Northfields Avenue.
